1 Great God, with wonder and with praise,
On all thy works I look;
But still thy wisdom, power and grace
Shine brighter in thy Book. 2 The stars that in their courses roll,
Have much instruction given;
But thy good Word informs my soul
How I may climb to heaven. 3 The fields provide me food, and show
The goodness of the Lord;
But fruits of life and glory grow
In thy most holy Word. 4 Here are my choicest treasures hid,
Here my best comfort lies;
Here my desires are satisfy'd;
And hence my hopes arise. 5 Lord, make me understand thy law,
Show what my faults have been;
And from thy Gospel let me draw
Pardon for all my sin.

